⁷Wibert, who was descended from a very influentia] family in northern Italy, had risen to the highest ecclesiastical dignity in Italy, the archbishopric of Ravenna. In the quarrel between Gregory and Henry he sided with the latter. In 1084, with Henry's help he was installed in Rome as antipope, taking the title Clement III. Shortly afterward, he crowned Henry as Em- peror and continued to dispute the papal title until his death in 1100.
